Disney's "Aladdin" topped the box office of the Chinese mainland market Friday, according to the China Movie Data Information Network Saturday. The live-action film grossed 27.37 million yuan (3.97 million US dollars) on the first day of its release. It was followed by Chinese concert film "Mayday Life," which took in 10.09 million yuan. Coming in the third was "Pokemon Detective Pikachu," which earned 8.26 million yuan. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star